8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 878,
9 L.D. 1355, “Resolve, to Require the Office of Tax Policy to Study Taxation of Renewable
10 Energy Infrastructure”
11 Amend the amendment by striking out all of the 4th, 5th and 6th instructional
12 paragraphs (page 1, lines 21 to 29 in amendment) and inserting the following:
13 'Amend the resolve in section 1 by striking out all of the indented paragraph (page 1,
14 lines 29 to 35 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
15 'The Governor's Energy Office shall consult with the Office of Tax Policy,
16 representatives from the renewable energy industry and other experts in the State and
17 municipal and county officials with relevant experience and solicit public comments on the
18 study. No later than November 4, 2026, the Governor's Energy Office shall submit a report,
19 including findings, recommendations and any suggested legislation, based on the study to
20 the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over taxation matters.
21 The joint standing committee may report out legislation related to the report to the 133rd
22 Legislature in 2027.' '
23 Amend the amendment by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
24 'Sec. 2. Funding. Resolved: That the Governor's Energy Office may receive funds,
25 grants or contributions from public or private sources to carry out the study required under
26 section 1. The Governor's Energy Office shall disclose its sources of funding as part of the
27 report required in section 1. The Governor's Energy Office is not required under this
28 resolve to undertake work for which it does not have or has not received sufficient funding.'
29 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
30 section number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment changes the report submission date from December 3, 2025 to
3333 November 4, 2026 and clarifies that the committee receiving the report is authorized to
3344 report out legislation based on the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027. The amendment
3355 also removes the appropriations and allocations section, allows the Governor's Energy
3366 Office to receive funds, grants or contributions from public or private sources to carry out
3377 the study and requires the office to disclose any funds it receives in its report to the
